f=Engineering/dev/custom/stack-profile/SKILL.md · in=stack-profile single per-business document describing *what business built with* languages, frameworks, hosting, datastores, mobile stack, CI/CD, connectors bound deployment (react+vercel, aws, flutter, HelixDB, whatever business actually runs). Engineering agent reads before acting, skills stay stack-agnostic stack lives config, baked method. constitution pattern applied technology choices. · p=Hardcoding stack skills makes team serve one company. stack-profile makes agents serve Next.js+Vercel SaaS, Flutter+Firebase mobile app, Rails+Postgres shop methods don't change, profile does. gives agent one source truth "how things here," raj's API conventions mia's framework patterns don't drift apart. · wu=Triggers: "stack profile," "what built with," "set our tech document," "what framework/host/db use," load step essentially Engineering skill. · st:/ Protocol=`Load the stack-profile (config path) \· -> If none: BUILD with the operator (template; real current stack, not aspirational) \· -> Agents read it before acting: raj reads API/backend, mia reads frontend, dana reads data, \· nova reads mobile, ops reads hosting/CI, aegis reads the security-relevant surface \· -> Stack CHANGES are ADRs (dev's architecture-decisions) — the profile is updated on adoption, versioned` · in=**Build reality.** Fill template what business *actually* runs today languages/versions, web framework host, backend API style, datastore(s), mobile stack (or "none"), CI/CD, auth, key third-party services, bound connectors. Aspirational entries ("we plan move to…") labeled such, never treated current. **One source truth.** agent reads relevant section; conventions (naming, error shapes, token usage) live point here, they can't diverge across agents. **Changes decisions.** Adopting new framework/datastore/host ADR first; acceptance, profile updated (version bump) change traces ADR number. **Detect drift.** Code introducing dependency pattern profile flagged either profile needs updating (via ADR) code off-standard. · of=profile follows `assets/stack-profile-template.md`. use, agents cite relevant section: "per stack-profile §Backend, APIs REST documented error shape." · pr=**Current reality, aspiration** aspirational entries labeled., **One document, read all** conventions don't fork across agents., **Stack changes ADRs** never silent; versioned, traced., **Drift finding** off-profile code gets flagged, absorbed., **Connectors named here** deployment bindings (which host, which connector, which CI) live profile tool skills know what exists. · f=profile urgent work proceed operator's verbally-stated stack, labeled provisional, start build., Multi-service business (different stacks product) one profile section service; shared conventions factored out., Profile stale after migration flagged; migration ADR updated it. · b:with Other Skills=`architecture-decisions` decides stack; documents current state agent reads it., Engineering skill consumes it: raj (backend/API), mia (frontend/tokens), dana (datastores including HelixDB playbook adopted), nova (mobile), ops (hosting/CI/monitoring), aegis (attack surface), rank (rendering/SEO-relevant framework facts)., Cross-department: mia's design-token section bridges atlas's brand kit; ops's hosting section board's infra-spend context lives.